  "reasoning": "Let the numbers of skateboards and bicycles be 7k and 4k. The difference is 7k - 4k = 3k, which equals 12, so k = 4. Then d = k + 6 = 10. Shuxin starts with 10 red, 7 yellow, and 3 blue candies. After eating some, let the equal remaining number of each color be n. Then 0 ≤ n ≤ 3 (since blue starts at 3). The total eaten is (10 - n) + (7 - n) + (3 - n) = 20 - 3n, which is smallest when n is largest, i.e., n = 3. Thus the smallest possible number of candies Shuxin ate is 20 - 3·3 = 11.",
